<TITLE> Depression forms over midwestern Bay </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 21 (bdnews24.com)  A depression has formed over the mid-western Bay of Bengal near the northern coast of the Indian states of Andhra Pradesh and Orissa, the meteorological office said Friday. The depression was 715 km from Chittagong seaport, 665 km from Cox's Bazar and 560 km southwest of Mongla Friday evening. It may further intensify and move towards the northwest, according to a met office forecast. The met office has asked Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla seaports to hoist local cautionary signal no 3. A met office special bulletin said the highest wind speed recorded within 44 km of the centre of the depression was 40 km per hour, which may increase to 50 km with gusty wind. Seas are expected to remain moderately choppy. All fishing boats and trawlers in the north Bay of Bengal have been asked to stay near the coast. bdnews
